Ahmed Idris, suspended accountant-general of the federation, was on Friday arraigned before a federal capital territory (FCT) high court on allegations of fraud. The Economic and Financial Crimes Commission (EFCC) preferred a 14-count charge of stealing and criminal breach of trust to the tune of N109.5 billion against Idris and three others. The other defendants are Godfrey Olusegun Akindele and Mohammed Kudu Usman, while a firm — Gezawa Commodity Market and Exchange Limited — is also listed in the charge. See photos below. <img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-727495" src="https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/Ahmed-Idris-Accountant-General11.jpg" alt="" width="1024" height="683" srcset="https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/Ahmed-Idris-Accountant-General11.jpg 1024w, https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/Ahmed-Idris-Accountant-General11-300x200.jpg 300w, https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/Ahmed-Idris-Accountant-General11-768x512.jpg 768w, https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/Ahmed-Idris-Accountant-General11-24x16.jpg 24w, https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/Ahmed-Idris-Accountant-General11-36x24.jpg 36w, https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/Ahmed-Idris-Accountant-General11-48x32.jpg 48w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /> <img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-727497" src="https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/Ahmed-Idris-Accountant-General10.jpg" alt="" width="1024" height="683" srcset="https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/Ahmed-Idris-Accountant-General10.jpg 1024w, https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/Ahmed-Idris-Accountant-General10-300x200.jpg 300w, https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/Ahmed-Idris-Accountant-General10-768x512.jpg 768w, https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/upload